description: From Latin innodatus, past participle of innodare, from in- (“in”) + nodus (“knot”).

verbs.description: innodate (third-person singular simple present innodates, present participle innodating, simple past and past participle innodated)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To bind up, as in a knot; to include.
examples: we do innodate with the like sentence of anathema
